external_knowledge:
- "added value exceeds the limit" implies that the value added to the process is greater than the maximum allowed value set in the process profile; 
- "occurred during the profile period" means the measurement timestamp falls within the start and end times of the profile; 
- "running processes" refers to processes with a status of 'Running'.

sql:
SELECT measurement_status
FROM process_measurements
WHERE measurement_status = 'Normal';

SELECT MAX(measurement_timestamp) AS most_recent_timestamp
FROM process_measurements
WHERE sensor_id = 1;

SELECT process_name, status
FROM processes
ORDER BY status;
